description: From the past participle stem of post-Classical Latin masticō (“I chew”), from Ancient Greek μαστιχάω (mastikháō, “I grind the teeth”).

verbs.description: masticate (third-person singular simple present masticates, present participle masticating, simple past and past participle masticated)

examples: The cow stood, quietly masticating its cud.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To grind or knead something into a pulp.
